parsedComplaintsResult.impact: TFI module failure can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to accidents or death.
symptoms: Vehicle completely shuts down and won't restart
engine quits instantaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause a fire, leading to vehicle damage or total loss.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the hood
alternator bursting into flames
arcing seen and heard within the alternator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring harness failure can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, melted fuses, and vehicle damage.
symptoms: All lights inside and outside the vehicle stay on
fuse burns and melts
electrical short in the alternator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failure can cause electrical problems, leading to fires.
symptoms: Ignition switch overheats
electrical problems due to the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Digital dash display issues can cause dimming or loss of lights, including the ABS light, which can affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: Lights on the digital dash display dim or go out
including the ABS light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Horn button issues can cause difficulty in locating and accessing the horn, which can affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: Difficulty in locating the horn button on the steering wheel
especially when the wheel is turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion or rusting of brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to loss of brake function, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
loss of rear brakes
emergency brake frozen and inoperable
vehicle pulling to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure (ABS, Calipers, Rotors, Pads)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of brake system components can cause loss of brake function, increased stopping distances, and accidents, especially in snowy or slippery conditions.
symptoms: ABS indicator light flashing intermittently
brake failure
vehicle pulling to one side while braking
difficulty stopping the vehicle
hard steering
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in serious harm or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle surges forward without warning
the vehicle takes off suddenly
the vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
the brake lights are on while the vehicle is accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard flashes or stays on
indicating a problem with the airbag system; the light may flicker
stay on for a few seconds
or blink in a specific pattern; the airbag may not deploy in an accident.
